---
import BlogLayout from '../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
---
<BlogLayout 
	title="Privacy Policy | WhyA11y"
	description="Our privacy policy explains how WhyA11y collects, uses, and protects your information when you visit our website. Learn about your rights and our data practices."
>
	<section id="privacy-content">
		<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2025</p>
		
		<h2>Our Privacy Commitment</h2>
		<p>
			At WhyA11y, we believe that privacy is a fundamental right. We are committed to 
			protecting your privacy and ensuring that your visit to our website is completely 
			private and secure.
		</p>
		
		<h2>No Data Collection</h2>
		<p>
			<strong>We do not collect, store, or process any personal information from our visitors.</strong> 
			When you visit WhyA11y, you can browse our content freely without worrying about 
			your data being tracked, stored, or shared.
		</p>
		
		<h2>What We Don't Do</h2>
		<p>We do not:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Collect personal information (names, email addresses, etc.)</li>
			<li>Use tracking cookies or analytics tools</li>
			<li>Monitor your browsing behavior</li>
			<li>Store your IP address or location data</li>
			<li>Use third-party advertising or tracking services</li>
			<li>Create user profiles or behavioral tracking</li>
			<li>Share any data with third parties</li>
		</ul>
		
		<h2>Local Storage Only</h2>
		<p>
			The only data stored on your device is your theme preference (light or dark mode) 
			using your browser's local storage. This information:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Stays on your device only</li>
			<li>Is never sent to our servers</li>
			<li>Can be deleted by clearing your browser data</li>
			<li>Is used solely to remember your visual preference</li>
		</ul>
		
		<h2>Server Logs</h2>
		<p>
			Like most websites, our hosting provider may maintain basic server logs for 
			technical purposes (ensuring the website works properly). These logs typically 
			include:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>IP addresses (for security and performance)</li>
			<li>Pages accessed</li>
			<li>Error messages</li>
			<li>Basic technical information</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			We do not have access to these logs, and they are not used for tracking or 
			identifying individual users.
		</p>
		
		<h2>Contact Information</h2>
		<p>
			If you choose to contact us via email (hello@whya11y.com), we will only use 
			your email address to respond to your message. We do not:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Store your email address in any database</li>
			<li>Add you to mailing lists without explicit consent</li>
			<li>Share your email with third parties</li>
			<li>Use your email for any purpose other than responding to your inquiry</li>
		</ul>
		
		<h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
		<p>
			Our website may contain links to external websites (like WCAG guidelines, 
			ARIA documentation, etc.). We are not responsible for the privacy practices 
			of these external sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies 
			when visiting them.
		</p>
		
		<h2>Your Privacy Rights</h2>
		<p>
			Since we don't collect personal data, there's no personal information to 
			access, modify, or delete. However, you can:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Clear your browser's local storage to remove theme preferences</li>
			<li>Use private/incognito browsing mode</li>
			<li>Disable JavaScript if you prefer (though some features may not work)</li>
			<li>Contact us with any privacy concerns</li>
		</ul>
		
		<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
		<p>
			Our website is accessible to users of all ages, including children. Since 
			we don't collect any personal information, there are no special restrictions 
			or concerns regarding children's privacy.
		</p>
		
		<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
		<p>
			If we ever change our privacy practices to collect data, we will:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Update this privacy policy immediately</li>
			<li>Clearly explain what data we collect and why</li>
			<li>Provide options for users to opt out</li>
			<li>Maintain transparency about our practices</li>
		</ul>
		
		<h2>Contact Us</h2>
		<p>
			If you have any questions about our privacy practices or this policy, 
			please contact us:
		</p>
		<p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@whya11y.com">hello@whya11y.com</a></p>
		<p>
			We're committed to maintaining your privacy and will be happy to address 
			any concerns you may have.
		</p>
	</section>
</BlogLayout>

<style>
	section {
		max-width: var(--container-md);
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0;
	}
	section h1 {
		font-size: var(--text-5xl);
		line-height: var(--leading-tight);
		margin: 0 0 var(--spacing-md);
		color: var(--fg);
	}
	.last-updated {
		color: var(--fg-muted);
		font-style: italic;
		margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
	}
	section h2 {
		font-size: var(--text-2xl);
		line-height: var(--leading-tight);
		margin: var(--spacing-xl) 0 var(--spacing-md);
		color: var(--fg);
	}
	section h3 {
		font-size: var(--text-xl);
		line-height: var(--leading-tight);
		margin: var(--spacing-2xl) 0 var(--spacing-sm);
		color: var(--fg);
	}
	section p {
		margin: 0 0 var(--spacing-md);
		line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
		color: var(--fg);
	}
	section ul {
		margin: var(--spacing-md) 0;
		padding-left: var(--spacing-2xl);
	}
	section li {
		margin: var(--spacing-sm) 0;
		line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
		color: var(--fg);
	}
	section a {
		color: var(--link);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-decoration-color: var(--link-underline);
		text-underline-offset: 0.2em;
		text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
	}
	section a:hover {
		color: var(--link-hover);
		text-decoration-color: var(--link-underline-hover);
		text-decoration-thickness: 3px;
	}
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		section h1 {
			font-size: var(--text-4xl);
		}
		section h2 {
			font-size: var(--text-lg);
		}
		section h3 {
			font-size: var(--text-lg);
		}
	}
</style>
